			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Higher-hanging fruit:  POSIX signal handling may well perform better than Mach exception handling on Mac OS X, since no Mach IPC or thread switching is required.  It would be good to measure the performance of both.  It might be worth switching to using POSIX signal handling for fault handling (and thread suspension) on Mac.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-02-21T17:57:10.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-02-21T17:57:10.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 1 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3317#c1" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3317/comments/full/1" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>